TextBody:
Hello William,
 
Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support.
 
To help us streamline the troubleshooting process and resolve your issue more efficiently, please provide the following information: 
Did you make any changes to the connection profile?
Which account did you use to launch the application? Is it yours or the service's account?
Does anyone else have access to the server?
Are you able to successfully launch NEA?
 
What software is currently installed - run this command from an admin Powershell prompt:
Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
 
To schedule a meeting, please use the link below.
https://nwxcorp.my.salesforce-sites.com/cts?Id=tZw5uANFTHZKIT4DWsegsSHpyTZu4nCJ5bLTQv.wog8-Z&MeetingID=g8z4RDOM18VdM8CFObIMsOza31.q0kS3KPJH_Xb24Io-Z
 
Thanks,

I don't believe any changes were made to a connection profile. The only change I recall making was to reporting on one of the reports/jobs. That was to email it to me to try and see if that would work but I have reverted it.

Typically, I RDP into the server using my account and open the application which I assume will also be from my account. If I login to any of the other pieces of the application I will use my username.
